{
  "text": "Procedure Employed for Catalysis Studies. The Lewis acid (30 \u03bcL of 100 mM solution in CH 3 CN, 3 \u03bcmol) or Br\u00f8nsted acid (30 \u03bcL of 300 mM solution in CH 3 CN, 9 \u03bcmol) was added to 1.21 mL of a 1.24 mM solution of 1 (1.5 \u03bcmol) in anhydrous CH [CITATION_1] Caution! Complete disproportionation of H 2 O 2 to oxygen and water can occur and hence the reactions should not be carried out in sealed vessels.",
